org.kepler.objectmanager

Class ObjectManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.kepler.objectmanager.ObjectManager

  • public class ObjectManager
extends java.lang.Object
    The ObjectManager searches through all of the NamedObj Objects in the workspace to see if any of them have a KeplerLSID associated with them.
    Author:
    Aaron Schultz

      • getHighestObjectRevision

        public NamedObj getHighestObjectRevision(KeplerLSID lsid)
                                  throws java.lang.Exception
        Return the NamedObj that has the highest revision number for a given LSID after searching through all the NamedObjs accessible by the ObjectManager. If no NamedObj is found at all then try to get the highest revision from the cache. If that doesn't find anything then return null. This method will replace the existing getObject(KeplerLSID) method
        Parameters:
        lsid -
        Returns:
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception
